This project presents a comprehensive analysis of hotel booking data using Power BI.
The objective is to derive actionable insights related to revenue performance, customer behavior, 
and booking trends to support strategic decision-making in the hospitality domain.

🎯 Objectives
Analyze key performance indicators such as Revenue, ADR, RevPAR, and Occupancy Rate
Understand customer segmentation and booking behavior
Evaluate revenue contribution across market segments and room types
Identify seasonal trends and demand patterns
Support data-driven pricing and operational strategies
📊 Dashboard Modules

1. Executive Overview

Provides a high-level summary of hotel performance:

Net Revenue
Total Bookings
Average Daily Rate (ADR)
Revenue per Available Room (RevPAR)
Occupancy Rate
Average Length of Stay
Revenue and Booking Trends (Monthly)
Revenue by Hotel Type and Market Segment

2. Booking Behaviour Analysis

Focuses on customer insights and booking patterns:

New vs Returning Guests
Customer Type Distribution
Guest Segmentation (Solo, Family, Business)
Booking Source Analysis
Lead Time Distribution
Stay Duration Analysis

3. Revenue & Pricing Analysis

Provides insights into revenue optimization:

Revenue Trend Over Time
Revenue by Room Type
ADR by Room Category
Revenue Contribution by Market Segment
Seasonal Revenue Analysis

4. Operational Insights

Analyzes operational efficiency and trends:

Cancellation Rate Analysis
Weekend vs Weekday Revenue
Special Requests Trend
Monthly Stay Patterns
Forecasting of Future Trends

🛠️ Tools & Technologies

Power BI Desktop – Data visualization and dashboard development
Power Query – Data cleaning and transformation
DAX (Data Analysis Expressions) – Calculated measures and KPIs
🔄 Data Preparation Workflow
Performed data cleaning by handling missing values and removing inconsistencies
Created derived columns such as stay duration and seasonal classification
Developed a structured data model with relationships
Implemented DAX measures for key metrics like Revenue, ADR, RevPAR, and Occupancy Rate
📈 Key Insights
Online Travel Agents contribute the highest share of bookings and revenue
City Hotels outperform Resort Hotels in terms of revenue generation
Revenue and bookings exhibit clear seasonal patterns
Majority of customers are first-time guests
Booking behavior varies significantly based on lead time and stay duration

🚀 Usage
Download the .pbix file
Open using Power BI Desktop
Use available slicers (Date, Hotel, Market Segment) for interactive exploration

📌 Conclusion

This project demonstrates the application of business intelligence techniques to transform raw booking data into meaningful insights, 
enabling better revenue management, customer understanding, and strategic planning in the hospitality industry.
